        <name>1.4.3.3 Add fractions 2</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;p class="HELM_exercise"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Simplify&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol class="HELM_parts"&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;\(\displaystyle {@exp1@} = \) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;\(\displaystyle {@exp2@} = \) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;\(\displaystyle {@exp3@} = \) [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]] [[feedback:prt3]]&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>&lt;ol class="HELM_parts"&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;The lowest common denominator is the product of the denominators, {@ev((v+a3)*(v+1),simp)@}. Thus writing both fractions with the same denominator we have:&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;\(\displaystyle {@exp1@} = \dfrac{@ev(a1*(v+1), simp)@}{@ev((v+a3)*(v+1),simp)@} + \dfrac{@ev(a2*(v+a3),simp)@}{@ev((v+a3)*(v+1),simp)@} = {@ta1@}.\)&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/li&gt;

    &lt;li&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;The lowest common denominator is the product of the denominators, {@ev((b1*v+1)*(b2*v+b1),simp)@}. Thus writing both fractions with the same denominator we have:&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;\(\displaystyle {@exp2@} = \dfrac{@ev(b1*(b2*v+b1), simp)@}{@ev((b1*v+1)*(b2*v+b1),simp)@} - \dfrac{@ev(b2*(b1*v+1),simp)@}{@ev((b1*v+1)*(b2*v+b1),simp)@} = {@ta2@}.\)&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/li&gt;
  
      &lt;li&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;The simplest expression having both denominators as its factors is {@(v-c1)^2@}. Thus writing both fractions with the same denominator we have:&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;\(\displaystyle {@exp3@} = \dfrac{@ev((v-1)*(v-c1), simp)@}{@(v-c1)^2@} + \dfrac{@v-1@}{@(v-c1)^2@} = {@ta3@}.\)&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/li&gt;

&lt;/ol&gt;</generalfeedback>
